  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Popliteal Sciatic nerve block is a regional technique that provides safe and reliable&#xD;
      perioperative anesthesia and analgesia of lower leg and foot used in diabetic patients.&#xD;
      Different additives have been used with local anaesthetics to achieve dense and prolonged&#xD;
      block. Magnesium sulfate possesses analgesic properties owing to its effect on NMDA&#xD;
      receptors.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
